						<td>
							<div style="width: 230px; float: left; position: relative;">
								<a href="site.do?siteId=143">The Best of Both Worlds: A Hybrid Approach to Calculating Value at Risk</a><br/>
								<div class="loupe">
									<a href="#abstractPaper-143" rel="abstractPaper143" title="Details of the article">
										<img alt="" src="images/icones/loupe.gif" />
									</a>
									<!-- Abstract publication -->
									<div id="abstractPaper-143" class="abstract-paper">
										<div class="top-abstract-paper">
											<div class="top-left-abstract-paper">Abstract</div>
											<div class="top-right-abstract-paper">Close</div>
										</div>
										<div class="abstract-separate-line"></div>
										<div class="middle-abstract-paper">
											<!-- description du site -->
											The hybrid approach combines the two most popular approaches to VaR estimation: RiskMetrics and Historical Simulation. It estimates the VaR of a portfolio by applying exponentially declining weights to past returns and then finding the appropriate percentile of this time-weighted empirical distribution. This new approach is very simple to implement. Empirical tests show a significant improvement in the precision of VaR forecasts using the hybrid approach relative to these popular approaches.
										</div>
										<div class="abstract-separate-line"></div>
										<div class="bottom-abstract-paper">
											
												
											
												
													
													
